<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-27T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-27T09:00:00-05:00" n="611" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760D.61/12–2745: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hulley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-27T16:00:00+02:00">December
                                    27, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>799. Shepherd tells me Orlov expressed to him few days ago his genuine
                            distress and disappointment at extent of anti-Soviet feeling in Finland
                            which trial of war responsibles has revealed. Evidently, Orlov set his
                            hopes too high on effectiveness of his efforts to win friends in
                            Finland, which from my observations have succeeded only in Left
                            circles.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hulley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>